  A side panel on the shuttle is pushed off as fire and rescue crews crawl over the area. Grimlock steps out of the shuttle in his T-Rex mode.

  Grimlock: Ok so me Grimlock don&#39;t fly well... Bring guests for Jotunn though.



Kraftlos &lt;kraftlos@...&gt; wrote:
          Within minutes of the crash, emergency calls poured on Salveo&#39;s local
lines. Atlantis fire crews had already redeployed to the scene.

&quot;At least we know where it is...&quot; he said, feeling the slow pang of
what humans would call a headache.

&quot;Perseus, you&#39;l be happy to know our shuttle&#39;s back,&quot; he said.
&quot;Unfortunately they decided to crash it into the emergency landing
site...&quot;

&quot;What is going on with Rodimus?&quot;

&quot;Nothing, no one will talk. I think we need to investigate....&quot;

&quot;Right. Try to get ahold of Doc or Guardia. We need to know their
status.&quot; he said. &quot;Dispatch a team to welcome our little run-aways
as well...&quot;

&quot;It would sure be nice to have people to dispatch....Salveo out...&quot;

On 1/10/08, Richard Allen &lt;roborick007@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; OOC: Zerg rush haha! Love the StarCraft reference.
&gt;
&gt; ::Grimlock::
&gt;
&gt; Grimlock: Actually we there almost. Prepare for landing.
&gt;
&gt; Just as Grimlock is setting the controls to land the stolen Atlantis
&gt; shuttle right back at the landing port he stole it from he gets the message
&gt; asking for a status report for Jotunn. Grimlock opens a return commlink.
&gt;
&gt; Grimlock: Me Grimlock here. Have Motherload and Airtankers with me.
&gt; Landing soon. Jotunn be ready.
&gt;
&gt; Grimlock closes the link and realizes that he hasn&#39;t radioed ahead to
&gt; tell Atlantis Air Traffic control who he is. Plus he is coming in way too
&gt; fast.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Oh well,&quot; he thinks.
&gt;
&gt; A moment later the shuttle has just short of crashed into emrgency landing
&gt; pads at the shuttle port.
&gt;
&gt; Grimlock: Any landing you can walk away from. Everybody walking?
&gt;
&gt; Nic &lt;warriorazure@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Lock-on sighed.
&gt;
&gt; Lock-on: Just great. The Minions pull a Zerg rush on us and manage
&gt; what they couldn&#39;t do since the last 100 teracycles. Well, there&#39;s no
&gt; wonder Jotunn wants Stormblaze!
&gt;
&gt; Skysword: Hey Grimy! Are we there yet? What about now? Are we there
&gt; yet? Are we there yet? Are we there yet? Huh?
&gt;
&gt; Motherload: Shut. Up. Skysword. LAST warning.
&gt;
&gt; --- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, Richard Allen &lt;roborick007@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; ::Grimlock::
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Grimlock pilots the shuttle into the air and heads for Atlantis.
&gt; He decided he liked the behavior and personality of these bots.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Grimlock: Minions hit city with missiles. Lots of em too. Sweep&#39;s
&gt; were everywhere. Maximals were out numbered and out gunned fast. City
&gt; tore apart bad. Cyclonus and Scourge, leaders, went for Rodimus Prime.
&gt; Rodimus fought Cyclonus alone on near island. He lose. Cyclonus make
&gt; somekind of light beam. Take Matrix from Rodimus. Rodimus seem real
&gt; hurt. Minions all leave then.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Nic &lt;warriorazure@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; The Airtankers follow him and get inside the shuttle.
&gt; Being fliers
&gt; &gt; themselves, this obviously bothered them.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Skysword: Screw that shuttle! This is too weird! I&#39;ll fly escort
&gt; outside.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Motherload: You will not do that. The situation clearly seems to call
&gt; &gt; for all of us intact, so you chew your pretty little comfort or I&#39;ll
&gt; &gt; shove it down your guzzler.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Being so rebuked, Skysword went in a corner to sulk. The three other
&gt; &gt; Airtankers were not pleased with the decision, but watching Motherload
&gt; &gt; being as irritable as Skysword about being stuck inside seemed to
&gt; &gt; convince them.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Lock-on: Grimlock, what did the Minions do during the fight?
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; --- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, Richard Allen &lt;roborick007@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; ::Grimlock::
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Grimlock: Ok. Me Grimlock take you all to Jotunn. He still at
&gt; &gt; Atlantis. Come on shuttle or fly if can.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Grimlock stomps back into the shuttle and transforms to robot
&gt; &gt; mode. He starts up the shuttle and is preparing for lift off.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Nic &lt;warriorazure@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt; The airtankers all looked at Grimlock with a slack-jawed
&gt; &gt; air and the
&gt; &gt; &gt; sense of impending doom they had dreaded. Add to that a touch of
&gt; &gt; &gt; pessimistic down mood, and that was as accurate a description of their
&gt; &gt; &gt; sparks as could be.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Lock-on: Holy sh...
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Motherload: Shut up. THAT wasn&#39;t anything I&#39;d expected... Gunrain, is
&gt; &gt; &gt; this accurate with the activity we&#39;ve been reported?
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Gunrain: Dam&#39; right &#39;twas... Ow... That ain&#39;t gonna do us no good,
&gt; &gt; Load...
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Motherload: It won&#39;t, but if we keep things like that, we&#39;re just
&gt; &gt; &gt; giving Unicron the keys to get in here and screw everything up.
&gt; &gt; &gt; Grimlock, take us to Jotunn.
